The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves feature extraction and classification, which are also related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the robustness of the method to noisy conditions, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM).
